Description: identity of pied babbler group - three letter code
identity of breeding season - single letter code, represents the time period September to March

Identity of each nest incubated - same identity applied to the brood if the eggs hatched. Code = Group ID, N for nest, number - for number of nest with 1 being the first clutch laid and incubated in the season, season ID
Number of days that the nest was incubated until the clutch either hatched or failed
Number of days that the nest was incubated until the clutch either hatched or failed, excluding all failed nests
Number of days that nestlings survived until the brood either fledged or failed
Number of days that nestlings survived until the brood either fledged or failed, excluding all failed nests
Number of days that the fledgling/s that survived the longest survived - 90 days if they reached nutritional independence, <90 days if they died before that
Total number of days between the start of incubation and nutritional independence or failure, cut-off at a maximum of 120 days
Whether or not brood failure occurred, where 0 = no failure, 1  = failure (Cox model requires that event = Death)
Whether or not the clutch hatched, where 0 = failed, 1 = hatched
Whether or not the clutch hatched, where 0 = hatched, 1 = failed (Cox model requires that event = Death)
Whether or not at least one chick from the brood fledged, where 0 = no fledglings, 1 = at least one fledgling
Whether or not at least one chick from the brood fledged, where 0 = at least one fledgling, 1 = no fledglings (Cox model requires that event = Death)
Whether or not at least one chick from the brood fledged, where 0 = no fledglings, 1 = at least one fledgling, excluding nests that did not hatch
Number of hatched nestlings if known
Number of nestlings that fledged
Mean daily maximum air temperature between start of incubation and hatching or clutch failure
Mean daily maximum air temperature between start of hatching and fledging or brood failure
Number of adult group members including both members of the dominant pair and all subordinate group members older than 1 year
Total rainfall in the 60 days prior to the start of incubation
Proportion of days between start of incubation and hatching equal to or exceeding 35.5 degrees C
Proportion of days between hatching and fledging equal to or exceeding 35.5 degrees C
Mean daily maximum air temperature between fledging and nutritional independence at 90 days or brood failure
Proportion of days between fledging and nutritional independence at 90 days or brood failure equal to or exceeding 35.5 degrees C
Total rainfall between fledging and nutritional independence
Number of consecutive seasons that the same two birds have made the dominant pair at the group
Number of consecutive seasons that the longest-running dominant individual in the group has been dominant in that or another group
Mean daily maximum air temperature between start of incubation and nutritional independence at 90 days or brood failure
Proportion of days between start of incubation and nutritional independence at 90 days or brood failure equal to or exceeding 35.5 degrees C
Total rainfall between 60 days before the start if incubation and nutritional independence at 90 days or brood failure
Whether or not the nest produced at least one fledgling that survived to nutritional independence at 90 days, where 0 = no fledglings survived, 1 = at least one fledling survived
Mean daily minimum air temperature between start of incubation and hatching or clutch failure
Mean daily minimum air temperature between start of hatching and fledging or brood failure
Mean daily air temperature variation (maximum - minimum) between start of incubation and hatching or clutch failure
Mean daily air temperature variation (maximum - minimum) between start of hatching and fledging or brood failure
Mean daily minimum air temperature between fledging and nutritional independence at 90 days or brood failure
Mean daily air temperature variation (maximum-minimum) between fledging and nutritional independence at 90 days or brood failure
